    "order": 1
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_0",
    "text": "Blackstone Takes Stake in Audit Firm",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.05092703111323307,
      0.2982791586998088,
      0.09135036205936183
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 2
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_1",
    "text": "BY MARK MAURER",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.012109623964308477,
      0.10312723800429696,
      0.09623964308476737,
      0.11012970478236651
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 3
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_7",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17654557042702357,
      0.10312723800429696,
      0.32950924155513067,
      0.14195909922813718
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_2",
    "text": "New Mountain Capital is selling its stake in accounting firm Citrin Cooperman to an investor group led by Black- stone, the fi rst flip of an audit firm by a private-equity inves- tor.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.11585899578260524,
      0.16443594646271512,
      0.16010185406222646
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_26",
    "text": "ter the North- western Mutual commitment. The firm was founded in 2009by 10 partners, many of whom had previously worked to- gether under Chief Executive Alan Waxman at Goldman Sachs. The partners were ini- snapping up a portfolio of mortgages in the aftermath of the financial crisis, for exam- ple. Now it is investing more consistently as banks have scaled back in response to regulatory pressure.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7144678138942001,
      0.11936022917164,
      0.8215423836838751,
      0.30333412906819446
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 6
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_13",
    "text": "Northwestern Mutual to take a small minority stake in investment firm",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3409815168897387,
      0.12222487467175937,
      0.4888463989802422,
      0.15946526617331105
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 7
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_19",
    "text": "pany it helped create in the aftermath of the 2008-2009 fi- nancial crisis. Other private- equity firms such as KKR, Blackstone and Brookfield have since bought insurers or struck deals to manage their assets.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5041427660930529,
      0.12254316861621707,
      0.6583811344805609,
      0.17315190578499243
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_27",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8330146590184832,
      0.12286146256067479,
      0.9859783301465902,
      0.167104320840296
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_24",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6666666666666666,
      0.12317975650513249,
      0.8209050350541747,
      0.20625447600859392
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_9",
    "text": "Blackstone, which manages about $55 billion in assets, would be one of the largest private-equity firms to have a stake in an accounting firm. A group led by Hellman & Fried- man, which managed $120 bil- lion in assets at the end of 2023, bought a stake in Baker Tily in June. Blackstone par- ticipated in the debt on that deal, providing $450 million of a $1 billion financing package.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17590822179732313,
      0.1429139810615103,
      0.3301465901848311,
      0.22535211267605634
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_3",
    "text": "The deal, which would value Citrin Cooperman at more than $2 billion, is the latest in a series of stakes that private-equity firms are taking in midsize audit and consult- ing firms in the U.S. Account- ing firms are hungry for more money to pay for technology and talent. Many private-eq- uity funds consider account- ing firms to be low-risk in- vestments that could net a sizable return based in part on recurring revenue streams.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012109623964308477,
      0.16073844195114187,
      0.16443594646271512,
      0.2562266252884539
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_14",
    "text": "BY MIRIAM GOTTFRIED",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.3409815168897387,
      0.1667860268958383,
      0.4435946462715105,
      0.17378849367390786
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_28",
    "text": "Dryden's group last month announced a deal to buy as much as $4 billion of loans from buy-now-pay-later plat- form Affirm.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8330146590184832,
      0.16742261478475373,
      0.9853409815168898,
      0.19893371528606668
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_22",
    "text": "For many firms, private $13B Amount of Northwestern Mutual's assets involved in the deal best opportunities arise. \"If someone gave me $13 billion and said go invest it to- morrow, I might be able to do it, but I probably wouldn't be able to do it in the best risk- adjusted-return way,\" said Mi- chael Muscolino, a Sixth Street co-founder who leads its financial-services efforts. Based in San Francisco, Sixth Street will manage more than $100 billion in assets af- tially backed by TPG but sepa- rated from it in 2020. Sixth Street built a team of 40 people focused on asset- based finance, hiring Michael Dryden from Credit Suisse in 2022 to lead its expansion. The firm had historically in- vested in asset-based finance in a more opportunistic way,",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5060548119821542,
      0.17410678761836557,
      0.65710643722116,
      0.20625447600859392
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 15
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_18",
    "text": "credit has largely been synon- ymous with lending to midsize companies, often to finance their buyouts by a private-eq- uity firm. As managers in- creasingly take in cash from in- surance compa- nies, they are moving deeper into strategies aimed at pro- viding better returns than corporate bonds while re- maining rela-",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5035054174633524,
      0.17506166945173868,
      0.5901848311026131,
      0.2944218986233787
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 16
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_15",
    "text": "Investment firm sixth Street is forging a partnership with Northwestern Mutual to manage $13 billion of the in- surer's assets, executives from the companies said. The money will primarily be in- vested in asset-based finance, a hot area that encompasses a swath of consumer lending, including mortgages, credit- card loans and auto loans.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3397068196303378,
      0.17951778467414659,
      0.4933078393881453,
      0.2565449192329116
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 17
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_29",
    "text": "Sixth Street has a separate team of 25 people solely fo- cused on insurance. It owns and advises on the invest- ments for Talcott Financial Group, an annuities company with $127 billion in assets.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8330146590184832,
      0.1995703031749821,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.24317657356568792
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 18
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_23",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5959209687699172,
      0.21071059123100183,
      0.727214786488209,
      0.27882549534495105
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 19
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_8",
    "text": "The sale allows New Moun- tain to focus on boosting reve- nue at Grant Thornton's U.S. unit, in which it acquired a stake last May. New Mountain aims to merge Grant Thorn- ton's nonaudit services in the U.S. and more than 10 other international units over the next five years, primarily in Europe and Asia, a person fa- miliar with the plans said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1752708731676227,
      0.22471552478714094,
      0.3301465901848311,
      0.30110607145699053
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 20
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_30",
    "text": "Northwestern Mutual is owned by its policyholders. The company, which was founded more than 165 years ago, provides life, disability- income and long-term-care in- surance, annuities, and bro- kerage and wealth advisory. It manages the bulk of its $627 billion in assets internally and has invested in private mar- kets for decades.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8330146590184832,
      0.24349486751014562,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.3195671202355375
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 21
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_4",
    "text": "The Blackstone-led group would take a more than two- thirds ownership stake in Cit- rin, and Blackstone itself holds an interest in the range of 40% to 45% in the group, peo- ple familiar with the transac- tion said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.25590833134399615,
      0.16379859783301465,
      0.30779024429060237
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 22
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_16",
    "text": "Milwaukee-based North- western Mutual also will take a small minority stake in Sixth Street, bolstering the invest- ment firm's balance sheet to help it fund growth. The stake is of a similar size to the roughly 10% holding Sixth Street bought back from pri- vate-equity firm TPG last year, according to people familiar with the matter.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3397068196303378,
      0.2562266252884539,
      0.49394518801784576,
      0.3322988780138458
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 23
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_20",
    "text": "tively low-risk. Insurers invest customers' premiums with the goal of earning more than they must pay out to policy- holders.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5047801147227533,
      0.294103604678921,
      0.6577437858508605,
      0.32625129306914935
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 24
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_25",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6673040152963671,
      0.2950584865122941,
      0.8215423836838751,
      0.3654014482374473
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 25
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_11",
    "text": "Regulators say they are concerned about potential conflicts of interest from the accounting profession's grow- ing ties to private equity, given that an auditor's objec- tivity is critical to the busi-",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17654557042702357,
      0.30078777751253283,
      0.32950924155513067,
      0.34885016312564654
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 26
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_5",
    "text": "Citrin Cooperman, a New York-based accounting firm, in October 2021 sold a majority stake to New Mountain, which has about $55 billion in assets under management.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.30747195034614466,
      0.16443594646271512,
      0.34503063579215404
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 27
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_31",
    "text": "But Northwestern Mutual didn't have the capability of finding and structuring asset- based finance deals, a labor- intensive process, according to Jeb Bentley, its chief invest- ment officer.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8330146590184832,
      0.3202037081244529,
      0.9847036328871893,
      0.36412827245961643
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 28
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_21",
    "text": "Unlike most of the deals done by its publicly traded ri- vals, Sixth Street's partnership with Northwestern Mutual will happen in phases, with money being invested as the",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5047801147227533,
      0.32625129306914935,
      0.6583811344805609,
      0.36444656640407413
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 29
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_17",
    "text": "Wall Street's big push into insurance got under way after Apollo Global Management began managing the assets of Athene, an insurance com-",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.33906947100063733,
      0.3329354659027612,
      0.4945825366475462,
      0.36444656640407413
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 30
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_6",
    "text": "Citrin Cooperman has grown significantly in the roughly four years since the sale. The firm reported $351.8 million in revenue in 2021. Its 2024 revenue totaled about $900 million, in part due to acquisitions of smaller firms, people familiar said.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.012746972594008922,
      0.34566722368106945,
      0.16443594646271512,
      0.3647648603485319
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 31
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_10",
    "text": "ness of accounting firms. The Financial Times first reported on the deal.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.17590822179732313,
      0.3469403994589003,
      0.32887189292543023,
      0.36444656640407413
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021",
    "order": 32
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_The Wall Street Journal - 2025-01-08@magazinesclubnew_page_021_32",
    "text": "CFTC Chairman to Step Down When Trump Takes Office",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
